what is DOM ?
DOM stands for document Object Module

DOM represents all HTML elements in the tree structure format .

Why DOM ?
dynamically change the content
add / remove elements
handle the user intersaction

Types of DOM's 
their are 4 types of DOM'
1.DOM Selectors :
    1.getElementbyID(" ")  : it selects only one element by its id only 
    2.getElementbyclass("") : it selects only by the class name
    3.getElementbyTagName("") : it selects only by the TagName
    4.getElementbyQuerySelector("") : in this queryselector we pass either id,name, if it matches output
                            will be generated in the way of process which one occur first it generates.
    5.getElementbyQuerySelectorall("") : it is same queryselector but it selects all

2. DOM Manipulation :
    1. Create element : it creates the element eg:document.createElement("element eg:div/p/label")
    2. remote element : it removes the element eg:document.getElementbyID("variable name").remove()
    3. replace element : it replace the element eg:document.getElementbyID("variable name").replace()
    
3. Attribute Manipulation :
    1.get Attribute():
    2.set Attribute():
    3.img.set Attribute():
    4.has Attribute():

4. Class Manipulation with Classlist :
    1.add
    2.remove
    3.toggle
